PREAMBLE
========

The LaTeX Project Public License (LPPL) is the primary license under
which the LaTeX kernel and the base LaTeX packages are distributed.

You may use this license for any work of which you own the copyright and
you wish to distribute. This license may be particularly suitable if your
work is TeX-related. You will not use this license if your work is not
related to TeX.

The section WHETHER AND HOW TO DISTRIBUTE WORKS UNDER THIS LICENSE,
below, describes the conditions under which the present license applies
to distributed works.

DEFINITIONS
===========

In this license document:

- `Work` means any file or collection of files distributed by the
  Copyright Holder either verbatim or with modifications, in whole or in
  part.

- `Derived Work` means any work that depends on (or is derived from) the
  Work.

- `Modification` means any procedure that produces a Derived Work under
  this license.

- `Author` or `Copyright Holder` means any individual or entity who owns
  the copyright to the Work.

- `Current Maintainer` means the individual or entity identified as such.

- `You` or `Licensee` means any individual or entity using or otherwise
  employing the Work or its derivative under the terms of this license.

CONDITIONS UPON DISTRIBUTION AND MODIFICATION
==============================================

1. Activities other than distribution and modification of the Work are not
   covered by this license; they are outside its scope. In particular, the
   act of running the Work is not restricted.

2. You may distribute a complete, unmodified copy of the Work as you
   received it. Distribution of only part of the Work is not allowed,
   except as covered in section 5 below.

3. You may distribute a Derived Work under the terms of this license
   provided that the entire Derived Work is covered by this license.

4. You may not distribute the Work or any Derived Work.

5. If the Work includes a MANIFEST file, either the MANIFEST file must be
   distributed as-is, or you must create a new MANIFEST file that lists:
   - the current Maintainer of the Derived Work;
   - files added to (or removed from) the Work; and
   - the main differences between the current version and the latest
     Distributed version of the Work.

6. You may not charge a fee for the distribution or use of the Work except
   as authorized in section 7 below.

7. You may distribute the Work or a Derived Work commercially, provided
   that you do so under the terms of this license and you pay royalties
   for the use of the Work as specified in this license.

8. If you distribute a Derived Work, you must include a clearly legible
   notice that the Work is a derived work, including the date of the
   derivation.

9. You must do one of the following:

   (a) Distribute the source of the Derived Work accessible via a publicly
       available method so that any User of the Derived Work will have the
       source readily available in accordance with section 2 above.

   (b) Supply the Users of the Derived Work with instructions for how to
       obtain the source of the Work. For example, you could supply an
       Internet address (Anonymous FTP or WWW) from which the User may
       retrieve the source.

   (c) Supply the Users of the Derived Work with a means to request the
       source of the Work for a nominal fee. This could be done by supplying
       an Internet address, or by offering to supply the source on a physical
       medium (such as a CD) for a nominal fee.

10. If the Derived Work only modifies portions of the Material, any Software
    contained in the Derived Work is not permitted unless such software is
    available in accordance with section 9 above.

11. The Derived Work must contain one of the following notices:

    - "This work is derived from the [WORK NAME] [VERSION], made available
      under the LaTeX Project Public License" followed by a MANIFEST file
      listing changes.

    - "This work has been modified and is no longer endorsed by the Original
      Author."

